==Old English==
===Etymology===
''Tiwes'' (''gen'' of [[Tiw|Tīw]]) + [[dæg|dæġ]].  Cognate with Old Frisian [[Tiesdei]], Old High German [[ziostag|zīostag]] (dialectal German [[Zistig]]), Old Norse [[tyrsdagr|týrsdagr]].  Used in translation of the Latin ''dies Marti'' ‘Mars’s day’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'tiwezdæj/

===Noun===
'''Tiwesdæġ'''
# [[Tuesday]]

